# Highest daily hops for one aircraft on one flight number

{{data_overview_md}}

{{result_table_md}}

The analysis reveals that the most extensive daily itineraries for a single aircraft under one flight number can consist of up to 8 consecutive hops in a single day. These longest routes are exclusively operated by Southwest Airlines (WN), reflecting their unique point-to-point network model that heavily utilizes multi-leg "through-flights" spanning multiple regions across the country.
